trapIdentifier.name: trapIdentifier
trapIdentifier.description: This object identifies the trap issued by the network element.

trapNetworkElemModelNumber.name: trapNetworkElemModelNumber
trapNetworkElemModelNumber.description: The value of this object is the model number of the network element. Combination of Model # and Serial # is used as the unique identifier of the NE.

trapNetworkElemSerialNum.name: trapNetworkElemSerialNum
trapNetworkElemSerialNum.description: The value of this object is the serial number of the network element. Combination of Model # and Serial # is used as the unique identifier of the NE.

trapPerceivedSeverity.name: trapPerceivedSeverity
trapPerceivedSeverity.description: This parameter defines five severity levels, which provide an indication of how it is perceived that the capability of the managed object has been affected. The other level is not a severity level, but indicates that an alarm has been cleared, and thus is no longer in alarm state. Note that this field has no meaning for configuration change traps.

trapNetworkElemOperState.name: trapNetworkElemOperState
trapNetworkElemOperState.description: The current Operational State of the Network Element which generated the trap.

trapNetworkElemAlarmStatus.name: trapNetworkElemAlarmStatus
trapNetworkElemAlarmStatus.description: The current Alarm Status of the Network Element Alarm Status is always equal to the highest severity level of all outstanding alarms in this NE.

trapNetworkElemAdminState.name: trapNetworkElemAdminState
trapNetworkElemAdminState.description: The current Adminsitrative state of the network element.

trapNetworkElemAvailStatus.name: trapNetworkElemAvailStatus
trapNetworkElemAvailStatus.description: The current Operational state of the network elment is defined in ISO/IEC 10164-2.

trapText.name: trapText
trapText.description: This variable contains an optional trap text.

trapNETrapLastTrapTimeStamp.name: trapNETrapLastTrapTimeStamp
trapNETrapLastTrapTimeStamp.description: This OBJECT IDENTIFIER is used to hold time since NE was 'CHANGED' last time. 'CHANGE' is defined as: 1) any write operation was performed on this NE which caused a trap. 2) any alarm was generated by this NE which caused a trap. 3) any alarm was cleared on this NE which caused a trap.

trapChangedObjectId.name: trapChangedObjectId
trapChangedObjectId.description: This variable identifies the object that has generated the trap.

trapAdditionalInfoInteger1.name: trapAdditionalInfoInteger1
trapAdditionalInfoInteger1.description: This 32 bit integer is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapAdditionalInfoInteger2.name: trapAdditionalInfoInteger2
trapAdditionalInfoInteger2.description: This 32 bit integer is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapAdditionalInfoInteger3.name: trapAdditionalInfoInteger3
trapAdditionalInfoInteger3.description: This 32 bit integer is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapChangedValueDisplayString.name: trapChangedValueDisplayString
trapChangedValueDisplayString.description: This DisplayString is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapChangedValueOID.name: trapChangedValueOID
trapChangedValueOID.description: This OBJECT IDENTIFIER is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapChangedValueIpAddress.name: trapChangedValueIpAddress
trapChangedValueIpAddress.description: This OBJECT IDENTIFIER is used to hold specific information about the trap.

trapChangedValueInteger.name: trapChangedValueInteger
trapChangedValueInteger.description: This 32 bit integer is used to hold specific information about the trap.

numberOfTrapReceivers.name: numberOfTrapReceivers
numberOfTrapReceivers.description: The number of managers to send traps to. This number can not exceed 4

trapReceiversTable.name: trapReceiversTable
trapReceiversTable.description: A list of managers to send traps to. The number of entries is given by the value of NumTrapReceivers. Maximum number of Trap Receivers is four.

trapReceiversTableEntry.name: trapReceiversTableEntry
trapReceiversTableEntry.description: The managers to send traps to.

trapReceiversTableIndex.name: trapReceiversTableIndex
trapReceiversTableIndex.description: The index to a trap receiver entry.

trapReceiverAddr.name: trapReceiverAddr
trapReceiverAddr.description: The IP address of the manager to send a trap to. NOTE: Changing TrapReceiverAddr FROM default value to anything else is equivalent of 'creating' of a new entry. Changing TrapReceiverAddr TO default value will result in deletion of that entry.

trapReceiverCommunityString.name: trapReceiverCommunityString
trapReceiverCommunityString.description: The community name to use in the trap when sent to the manager.

trapToBeSendQueueSize.name: trapToBeSendQueueSize
trapToBeSendQueueSize.description: The agent maintains 2 queues: TrapsToBeSendQueue and TrapsSentQueue. The SNMP agent can receive a burst of traps which need to be sent to the network manager. The SNMP agent will put them in TrapsToBeSendQueue and from there hi will send traps to the a manager at throttling rate. The traps will be kept in sequence by the time at which they came in.

trapSentQueueSize.name: trapSentQueueSize
trapSentQueueSize.description: The agent maintains 2 queues: TrapsToBeSendQueue and TrapsSentQueue. The SNMP agent maintains Trap History (TrapsSentQueue) by saving last 'X' sent traps.

trapThrottlingRate.name: trapThrottlingRate
trapThrottlingRate.description: The number of traps agent can send to a particular manager (trapReceiver) per second.

trapLastSent.name: trapLastSent
trapLastSent.description: This variable contains the last trapIdentifier (sequence number) agent sent to this manager. Upon startup agent will send cold-start trap and sat value of TrapLastSent to 1.

trapReceiversEntryOperState.name: trapReceiversEntryOperState
trapReceiversEntryOperState.description: The current Operational State of this entry in TrapReceivers Table.

trapResendRequest.name: trapResendRequest
trapResendRequest.description: The manager may write this object when the indicated trap (indicated via trapIdentifier) should be resent. It is not intended to be read by the manager, but is read-write for compatability with older SNMP compilers.

numberOfDiscriminators.name: numberOfDiscriminators
numberOfDiscriminators.description: The number of EFDs (filters) agent has in it's database. This number can not exceed 20

trapDiscrimTable.name: trapDiscrimTable
trapDiscrimTable.description: A list of EFDs (trap filters). Before forwarding trap to a trapReceiver (manager) agent filters all traps acording to all EFDs defined for this manager.

trapDiscrimTableIndex.name: trapDiscrimTableIndex
trapDiscrimTableIndex.description: The index to a trap discriminator entry.

trapDiscrimReceiverAddr.name: trapDiscrimReceiverAddr
trapDiscrimReceiverAddr.description: The IP address of the manager this Discrim belongs to. It should be equal to TrapReceiverAddr. NOTE: Changing TrapDiscrimReceiverAddr FROM default value to anything else is equivalent of 'creating' of a new entry. Changing TrapReceiverAddr TO default value will result in deletion of that entry.

trapDiscrimAvailabilityStatus.name: trapDiscrimAvailabilityStatus
trapDiscrimAvailabilityStatus.description: This object reflects the current Availability status of the Discrim (based on ISO/IEC 10164-2).

trapDiscrimWeeklyMask.name: trapDiscrimWeeklyMask
trapDiscrimWeeklyMask.description: This object represents weekly scedule for corresponding Discrim. The WeeklyMask consists of 7 numeric characters (1 for each day of the week). Each numeric character can take a value of eather '1' - enabled or '2' - disabled. For example, with WeeklyMask='1122221', an agent will aplly corresponding Disriminator only on Mondays, Tuesdays and Sundays. Any characters other than '1' and '2' will be ignored.

trapDiscrimDailyStartTime.name: trapDiscrimDailyStartTime
trapDiscrimDailyStartTime.description: This object represents daily start time for corresponding Discrim. The StartTime is expressed as an offset (in minutes) from 2400 hours military time. For example, StartTime=70 represents start time of 1:10 AM.

trapDiscrimDailyStopTime.name: trapDiscrimDailyStopTime
trapDiscrimDailyStopTime.description: This object represents daily stop time for corresponding Discrim. The StopTime is expressed as an offset (in minutes) from 2400 hours military time. For example, StopTime=70 represents stop time of 1:10 AM.

trapSeverityDiscrim.name: trapSeverityDiscrim
trapSeverityDiscrim.description: The severity threshold of traps to be send to the manager. Only traps of equal or greater severity than this value are sent to the manager.

trapDiscrimOperationalState.name: trapDiscrimOperationalState
trapDiscrimOperationalState.description: The current Operational State of the Discriminator.

trapDiscrimConfigChangeCntl.name: trapDiscrimConfigChangeCntl
trapDiscrimConfigChangeCntl.description: This variable turns reporting of configuration changes on or off.
